div.div: Chester-East Lincoln CCSD #61 would like to determine approximately how many kindergarten students to expect for the 2020-2021 school year. If you live in Chester-East Lincoln CCSD #61 and have a child who will be five years old on or before September 1, 2020, please contact Chester-East at (217)732-4136 to be added to our mailing list for kindergarten registration information. Before entering in the fall, students are required to have a current physical and immunization record, dental and eye exam, and a certified birth certificate on file. If you have a concern or question about your son/daughter's readiness for kindergarten, CEL will be conducting Pre-K screenings in March. Please call the office at (217)732-4136 to set up an appointment.

br.br:
We want to inform you that we have made some changes in our district to be
compliant with the recent changes through HB3586 (legislation).
If your child receives a related service, like speech, occupational therapy, physical
therapy, counseling through the school, or other related services, service logs are
available upon request.
